<P>
NATIONAL VIDEO RENTALS ; SUSPENSE EDGES OUT 'SLEEPLESS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Once the romantic glow of Valentine's Day faded, so did "Sleepless in 
Seattle." Rentals briefly shot "Sleepless" into the top spot, but this week it 
slipped to No. 4.Seems renters are in an action/suspense mood these days, with 
four out of Top Five falling into that category. "In the Line of Fire," with 
John Malkovich's Oscar-nominated performance, moved to the top. "Last Action 
Hero" seems to have peaked, slipping a notch to No. 3--it's attracted 
considerable renter interest, in spite of its disappointing box-office 
performance, but has nowhere near the appeal of the usual Schwarzenegger action 
movie. The college-football drama "The Program," notorious for its macho, 
lying-in-the-road sequence (not included in the rental video), debuted at No. 
20. So far, "The Real McCoy," starring Kim Basinger, is no blockbuster, moving 
up just two notches to No. 19.  
</P>
<P>
 * In his directorial debut, Mel Gibson also stars, playing against his image, 
in "The Man Without a Face." This quiet little drama about a recluse with a 
scarred face, didn't earn Gibsonesque box-office numbers--its $23.1 million is 
about as much as a "Lethal Weapon" movie would make in its first week or so. 
The video opened at No. 14 and Gibson's star power should easily make it a Top 
10 rental--maybe even Top Five. Source: Billboard Publications Inc. 03,29,06,08 
