<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL UNIFORMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Thank you for the thoughtful editorial (Feb. 22) on uniform requirements for 
our schools. I think there is no question that we would see an immediate 
benefit in attitude and safe passage to and from campus. 
</P>
<P>
 If the remaining question is one of costs, I have what I feel is a realistic 
solution. We have always let license plates be made in our prisons, so why not 
move in some sewing machines? Just think, former gang members making clothing 
to preclude their younger siblings from joining them. 
</P>
<P>
 There is another beneficial byproduct. We would be offering training in the 
clothing industry for employment after their parole. This could serve to bring 
back some employment we currently lose to other labor forces. So far, I have 
never seen a master license plate maker gain work in the private sector. 
</P>
<P>
 DAVE THATCHER 
</P>
<P>
 San Fernando 
</P>
</TEXT>
