<HEADLINE>
<P>
UC IRVINE PAYS PRICE FOR LETDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine managed to maintain the momentum from Saturday's upset of New Mexico 
State for much of Thursday's game against UC Santa Barbara.But the few minutes 
the Anteaters let down proved disastrous. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anteaters (7-18, 4-13), after taking a nine-point halftime lead by forcing 
11 turnovers, reverted to their midseason propensity for going scoreless for 
extended periods, and were outscored, 16-0, in the first five minutes of the 
second half in losing, 81-77, in a Big West game before 2,259 at the Bren 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Brown (22 points) led a furious rally from a 20-point, second-half 
deficit before Santa Barbara (13-15, 9-8) held on to win. JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
