<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; LEE'S LATE BIRDIES LEAD VALENCIA TO VICTORY OVER SERVITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Lee birdied the last three holes to give Valencia a 414-415 victory over 
Servite in an 18-hole nonleague match that concluded Thursday at Alta Vista 
Country Club in Placentia. 
</P>
<P>
 The first round was held Tuesday at Hacienda Golf Club in La Habra Heights. 
Lee made a 15-foot putt on the final hole to give Valencia the victory. Lee and 
teammate James Wooley were paired on the second day of competition and both 
shot a one-under 35. Wooley had a two-day total of 75 and Lee shot 76. 
</P>
