<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; SADDLEBACK ROUTS ORANGE COAST, 13-2 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback scored 11 runs in the first three innings and went on to beat 
Orange Coast, 13-2, in an Orange Empire Conference baseball game Thursday at 
OCC. 
</P>
<P>
 Lorne Rosas had a three-run double in the first for Saddleback (7-5, 2-1 in 
conference), which scored six times in the inning.The Gauchos added one in the 
second and four more in the third. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrick Antrim had three hits, Wade Jackson, and Rosas had two hits and Ted 
Wilkes had a home run for Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
 Dennis Crine (2-1) allowed four hits and had nine strikeouts in seven innings 
for Saddleback. Orange Coast is 3-8, 0-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Orange Empire Conference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 13, Fullerton 4 -- Israel Gonzalez went four for five, including three 
doubles, drove in three and scored three for host Cypress (13-4, 1-1). Eric 
Stevens added a three-run home run for the Chargers. Cypress scored eight runs 
in the sixth to take a 12-1 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Tim Walker had a pinch-hit two-run home run in the eighth inning for Fullerton 
(7-7-1, 1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 10, Golden West 6 -- Rancho Santiago (14-2, 2-0) ran its 
winning streak to 11 games with a home victory. Jamie Estrada had a single, 
double and home run and drove in six runs for the Dons. 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 6, Cypress 0 -- Laura Kesterson pitched a one-hitter and improved 
to 12-1 for host Saddleback (12-3, 2-0). Cheri Davis had a two-run home run in 
the second and a two-run double in the third for Saddleback. Shawna Bray and 
Lucy Jacobs each added two hits and an RBI. 
</P>
