<P>
COLOMBIA TO TRAIN AT CAL STATE FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Colombia, one of the dark-horse favorites to win this year's World Cup, will 
establish its official training site at Cal State Fullerton, it was announced 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Three other World Cup soccer teams also named their official training sites, 
with Romania being based at UC Irvine, Sweden at Loyola Marymount and Cameroon, 
a 1990 World Cup quarterfinalist, at Oxnard College. 
</P>
<P>
 The United States, the fifth Southland-based team, will continue to use its 
national training camp in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
