<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police have concluded a two-month investigation into methamphetamine dealers 
in Ventura and Santa Paula with the arrest of three people and the seizure of 
five pounds of the drug, authorities said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ramiro Juarez, 38, and Anna Prado, 30, both of Santa Paula, and Manuel 
Gutierrez were taken into custody about 3 p.m. Wednesday in a parking lot near 
the intersection of Seaward Avenue and Harbor Boulevard.Police did not know 
Gutierrez's age or hometown. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura Police Sgt. Bill Bogner said the three, who he described as wholesale 
traffickers, were in the parking lot waiting to sell the drugs to other 
dealers. 
</P>
<P>
 During the arrests, police found five one-pound packages of the powdered 
substance inside the car. The street value of the drugs was estimated at 
$200,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The arrests were made without incident, Bogner said, with the help of about 18 
officers from Ventura, Oxnard and Santa Paula and agents from the U. S. Drug 
Enforcement Administration. 
</P>
<P>
 All three suspects are being held in federal custody in Los Angeles, Bogner 
said. JULIE FIELDS 
