<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA: MOORPARK; REVIEW POLICY FOR PROPOSED LAWS OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES MAIELLA JR. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hoping to avoid gaps in the city's review of ordinances, the Moorpark City 
Council has adopted a procedure ensuring that all proposed local laws undergo 
the same scrutiny before they get to the council for action. 
</P>
<P>
 The policy ensures that every proposed ordinance receives a full review by 
staff members, the city manager and city attorney before winding its way onto 
the council dais. 
</P>
<P>
 "It just puts the whole thing into context and shows the flow of approvals and 
cycles," Mayor Paul Lawrason said of the new procedure. "I think this comes 
from the fact that some things have been brought to us that really weren't 
ready for City Council attention." JAMES MAIELLA JR. 
</P>
