<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOCUSED CALABASAS NOT BUFFALOED IN 4TH TRY AT FRONTIER OPPONENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KENNEDY COSGROVE, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When top-seeded Moorpark faces Calabasas today, it will mark the second year 
in a row the Southern Section Division V boys' soccer championship match will 
feature two Frontier League teams. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, Santa Paula defeated the Coyotes in the title match, the third time 
since 1986 that Calabasas lost in the final to a Frontier opponent. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas Coach John Reich was asked if he felt any special sense of urgency 
to win this matchup at Gahr High. 
</P>
<P>
 "You mean I may be the Marv Levy of high school soccer coaches?" he said with 
a laugh, referring to the coach of the Buffalo Bills, three-time Super Bowl 
losers.  
</P>
<P>
 "No, the focus has been to play as well as we can. We are very comfortable 
that we can play with Moorpark." 
</P>
<P>
 The Musketeers (26-2-1) and the Coyotes (13-3-2) met twice this season.  
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark, the Frontier League champion, won the first meeting, 2-0, and the 
teams tied, 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 The Coyotes are led by senior defender Jeff Toms, senior forward Shayne 
Ferber, senior midfielder Bhret Haessig and junior goalkeeper Mike Freedman 
(eight shutouts). 
</P>
<P>
 Junior forward Pat Russo leads Moorpark with 28 goals. Senior forward Curtis 
Silverest has 19 goals, senior midfielder Brody Trejos has 18 and senior 
midfielder Paul Dojo has 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
