 COACH: Pat Tellers 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 21-54 04,20,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS YR. POS. B-T Jeff 
Avichouser Sr. LF R-R Adam Chez Sr. 2B R-R Adam Ferry Sr. CF R-R Joey Gomez Sr. 
SS-P R-R Eric Julin Sr. RF R-R J.R. Rodriguez Jr. 3B R-R TOP RETURNERS YR. POS. 
B-T David Haller Jr. OF R-R Steve Lopez Sr. 1B L-L Randy McDaniel Jr. C R-R 
Chris Pope Sr. C R-R 04,16,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. POS. B-T Chris Anderson 
Jr. C R-R Ryan Jones Jr. INF. R-R David Miller Sr. 1B R-R Ryan Owens So. 2B-P 
R-R Marc Portino Jr. 3B-P R-R OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Tellers believes the league will be tough this season, but with 10 returning 
starters, he also thinks his team can weather the storm. "Our returning players 
have lots of playing experience, but pitching will be the key," Tellers said. 
Although he thinks the Raiders will do well on offense and defense, he admits 
his team will need luck on its side if it is going to make a title run. Last 
year, the Raiders finished last (3-12), but still managed to place four players 
on first and second all-league teams. Although Sonora lost two key players in 
Todd Vorrell and Peter Lythgoe to graduation, Tellers has a feeling this team 
might surprise some people. "We didn't get much (luck) last year," he said, 
noting that eight games were lost by one run. "It's tough to lose by one . . . 
but eight games?" Nevertheless, Tellers will try to keep the team focused and 
hope for some good pitching. 
</P>
