<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL '94: FREEWAY LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 BUENA PARK 
</P>
<P>
 1993 RECORDS: 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 18-6 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 10-5 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: Dave Meggison 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 51-39 
</P>
<P>
 RETURNING STARTER: Greg Cabral 
</P>
<P>
 YR.: Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 POS.: SS 
</P>
<P>
 B-T: R-R 04,20,05,06,05 TOP RETURNERS YR. POS. B-T Chris Baca Sr. C R-R Danny 
Baca Jr. P L-L Robert Capps Sr. IF R-R Timmy Jones Jr. OFF L-R TOP NEWCOMER YR. 
POS. B-T Francisco Espinosa Sr. P R-R OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Meggison, a fourth-year coach, knows the feeling of having to start rolling 
that rock up the hill again. For him, it's called a rebuilding year. From being 
close to the top of the heap, to being at the bottom. "We lost some very 
important people last year," said Meggison, whose team finished second in 
league in 1993 with a record of 18-6, 10-5. "A big loss for us was Alfredo 
Garcia, who was MVP of the Freeway League, all-county, All-Southern Section, 
MVP of the Orange County All-Star game and led the county in earned-run 
average. "It's hard to replace someone of that caliber." Also graduating was 
all-league pitcher Alfonse Flores and shortstop Jason Cabral. In all, seven 
starters are gone. Nevertheless, Meggison is straight forward about the 
situtation. "When you have 10 freshmen and 11 sophomores, you have no illusions 
about things," he said. That's not to say this year will be a waste. Far from 
it, he said, noting that rebuilding is part of the grand scheme. He does expect 
some good things from Greg Cabral, Jason's younger brother. Meggison expects 
Cabral to be one of his key players at shortstop. The league will be tough with 
Troy, Fullerton and La Habra. "We've got some young kids this year. And I'm 
sure we'll make lots of mistakes. But in time these kids will learn and get 
better. We'll be back." 
</P>
</TEXT>
