<P>
 TROY 03,14,09,08 1993 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 19-6 13-2 COACH: Dane Ilertsen 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 62-39 04,20,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS YR. POS. B-T Brad 
Downing Sr. RF R-R Jim Hostetler Sr. P R-R Brian Logan Sr. CF R-R Rick 
Parmenter Sr. P R-R Rich Richey Sr. 3B R-L Nick Ruzzi Sr. CF R-R Greg Western 
Sr. P R-R TOP RETURNER YR. POS. B-T Justin Bero Sr. OF R-R 04,15,05,06,05 TOP 
NEWCOMERS YR. POS. B-T Trevor Brown Sr. 2B R-R Chad Elliott So. OF R-L Kevin 
Gray Jr. P/SS R-R OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Ilertsen calls the Freeway League "well balanced," and said any team could 
make the playoffs. But don't be fooled by the humble fifth-year coach. Among 
the opposition, all agreed that Troy will once again be the team to beat. For 
starters, the Warriors have a strong contingent of returning starters, 
including Logan at catcher, Richey at third base, Ruzzi in center field, 
Downing in right field and all-league pitcher Parmenter. Troy easily took the 
league title last year and placed three players on the all-league first team 
and three more on the second. And though Troy stumbled in first round of the 
Southern Section Division II playoffs, losing to Redondo Beach Redondo Union, 
9-7, in extra innings, the fact that Redondo eventually lost to champion Lompoc 
made the defeat a little easier to take. But this year, Ilertsen said his team 
might go all the way. Along with the core of returners, he is expecting some 
help from several newcomers, including outfielder Elliott, pitcher/shortstop 
Gray and second baseman Brown. 
</P>
