Now, moving on to his team. Like Buena Park, the Lancers will feature several 
new faces this season. And like the Coyotes, Sunny Hills has lost some key 
players to graduation. Six starters are gone, which for any team is a big loss. 
But every team has to go through a rebuilding stage, and this time it's Sunny 
Hills' turn. But Elliott isn't pulling out his hair. The Lancers have some good 
returning players in juniors Hochgesang at shortstop, Monson at second base and 
senior Wescott, who is moving from outfield to play third base. On paper, the 
Lancers shouldn't be as far removed from the race as Elliott makes it sound, 
and with senior pitcher Herrera back, this could also be a important factor in 
giving the Lancers strength at a position which for now is an unknown. 
</P>
