<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARATHON TO CLOSE STREETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Marathon, which starts at 840 a.m. Sunday, will force many 
street closures in central Los Angeles. Because of the added congestion, 
motorists are ask to avoid the I-10 between the 110 and 405 freeways from 9 
a.m. to 3:45 p.m. Motorists are also asked to avoid unnecessary travel in the 
La Brea Avenue / Crenshaw Boulevard corridor. Off-ramps will be closed on the 
I-10 at Crenshaw, the 101 at Vine, Gower and Hollywood and the 110 at 6th. 
</P>
