<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; CITY TO HOLD PUBLIC MEETING AT LIBRARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council will hold a special public meeting March 11 in the Newport 
Center Library's community room to discuss the city's budgetary outlook, city 
officials said Thursday.  
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will begin at 8 a.m. and last all day, City Manager Kevin J. 
Murphy said, adding that it is a continuation of the special meetings held Jan. 
14 and 15 at the Balboa Bay Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Those Balboa Bay Club meetings have caused a minor controversy among at least 
two residents who have claimed that the city did not properly notify the 
public. Murphy said that the council had publicly adjourned the Jan. 10 meeting 
to the Balboa Bay Club four days later and then held the meeting at the club 
with "the door wide open and the agenda at the back" of the room. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was not a secret meeting," Murphy said. "Far from it." BOB ELSTON 
