<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; FOG TO HANG AROUND AGAIN THIS MORNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The early morning fog that blanketed coastal Orange County on Wednesday and 
Thursday is expected back today, according to WeatherData, which provides 
forecasts for The Times. 
</P>
<P>
 An area of low pressure about 700 miles to the southeast is creating an 
onshore flow of moist marine air, according to meteorologist Bruce D. Thoren of 
WeatherData.As the night air cools, the moisture in the air condenses and fog 
develops, he said. The fog may continue through the weekend, Thoren said.  
</P>
<P>
 The forecast for today calls for morning clouds and patchy fog, giving way to 
partly sunny skies, with some low cloudiness, later in the afternoon. Farther 
inland, Thoren said, particularly in the canyons, the morning fog should 
diminish. 
</P>
<P>
 In Newport Beach, this morning's low is expected to be 50 degrees, with an 
afternoon high of 61. Santa Ana is expected to have a morning low of 49, with 
the mercury rising to 76. MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
