ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; ROBBERY SUSPECT HELD AFTER CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man suspected of stealing a motor home Thursday and later taking a car at 
knifepoint was arrested after a chase and crash, Brea police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gerald William Maston, 25, of Costa Mesa was taken to the jail ward at Western 
Medical Center-Anaheim for observation after the stolen Honda Civic he was 
driving along Santa Ana Canyon Road hit a tree, left the road and landed upside 
down in an eastbound lane of the Artesia Freeway, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident began when Brea police found a motor home that had been reported 
stolen earlier in Huntington Beach. It was abandoned and stuck in the sand at 
Featherly Regional Park. 
</P>
<P>
 While Officer Dave Wearp was investigating the motor home, a woman in a nearby 
home reported to police that a man with a knife had entered her home and forced 
her to give him cash and the keys to her Honda. Wearp said he saw a Honda 
driving by the park and pursued it along Gypsum Canyon Road. The Honda turned 
onto Santa Ana Canyon Road and accelerated before swerving into the tree. MARK 
