<P>
 T-Bill Rates Up: Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills rose to their 
highest level in nearly two years.The average discount rate was 4.03%, up from 
3.59% at the last auction a month ago. It was the highest rate since 52-week 
bills averaged 4.07% on May 28, 1992. The bills will carry an equivalent coupon 
interest rate of 4.22%, with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,592.50. 
Sales totaled $16.52 billion out of bids of $43.98 billion. 
