<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL STUDENTS WIN TV AWARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Students from USC are among the winners of the 15th annual College Television 
Awards. 
</P>
<P>
 First-prize winners receive $1,000 from the Academy of Television Arts & 
Sciences and a product grant of $2,000 from Kodak. They will be honored at a 
dinner in Beverly Hills on March 13. 
</P>
<P>
 In the information category, the winners were Sharon Rennert of USC, Lisa L. 
Bernhard of Regent University in Virginia Beach, Va., and Brian Conybeare, 
Kevin Howatt, George Jerjian, Lisa Low and Hong Zhang of New York University. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin Curland of USC won a second-place award in the entertainment category, 
and Keith Llorens, Dorothy Thurman and Errol Watson of Cal State Dominguez 
Hills shared second in the information category. 
