<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; DRIVER SOUGHT AFTER 2 ON MOTORCYCLE HIT, 
KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHAU LAM, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are seeking a driver whose vehicle struck a motorcyclist and his 
passenger, who were lying in the roadway after crashing into a van, said a 
California Highway Patrol spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant Gray, 40, and Mary Krone, 38, both of Granada Hills were pronounced dead 
at the scene of the 10:21 p.m. Wednesday crash on the Golden State Freeway near 
Rye Canyon Road in Santa Clarita. 
</P>
<P>
 According to witnesses, Gray's motorcycle rear-ended a van traveling 55 m.p.h. 
south on the freeway, CHP Officer Wendy Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gray and Krone, both wearing helmets, were struck by at least one car after 
being ejected from the motorcycle, Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We don't know if they were killed when they hit the pavement or when they 
were struck by another car," Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
 The coroner's office has not released the cause of death. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the van, Carlos Carrillo, 32, of Dinuba was treated at the scene 
for minor injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are investigating the incident as a hit-and-run. 
</P>
</TEXT>
