<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUNWAY TO REALITY: SLIP ONE OVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOANNA DENDEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Look: The short slip dress is making a comeback -- this time over a 
sleeveless T-shirt. With spaghetti straps and above-the-knee hemline, it's a 
sure bet for the spring-summer wardrobes of cute young things with near-perfect 
bodies. 
</P>
<P>
 How to Do It Big: Who would have guessed that Ralph Lauren would design little 
slip dresses for his spring collection? He showed them in solids and tiny 
floral prints with Ts of varying sleeve lengths and thigh-high stockings. 
</P>
<P>
 One of his simplest versions of the look is a black jersey knit dress over a 
white, skinny-ribbed "muscle-man" model T. The dress may be skimpy, but the 
price isn't -- $335. The shirt is $20. Both are available in Beverly Hills at 
the Polo/Ralph Lauren boutique. 
</P>
<P>
 Total: $355 
</P>
<P>
 How to Do It Budget: The clever designers who make moderately priced clothing 
have pounced on the slip dress. 
</P>
<P>
 Francine Browner does one in black rayon knit for her Hearts line. The best 
thing about her Ralph Lauren look-alike is that it comes with a white 
cap-sleeved T-shirt. The set costs $59 at Windsor Fashions in the Westside 
Pavilion, Los Angeles. To duplicate the Lauren look, simply sub in a Hanes 
sleeveless T-shirt; a pack of three costs $7 at K mart stores citywide. 
</P>
<P>
 Total: $61.33 JOANNA DENDEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
